01:22:02,584 --> 01:22:06,087
? ?

1807
01:22:06,087 --> 01:22:07,088
It's empty.

1808
01:22:07,088 --> 01:22:08,590
Nobody here.

1809
01:22:18,600 --> 01:22:21,603
? ?

1810
01:22:25,607 --> 01:22:28,610
(classical music playing)

1811
01:22:31,613 --> 01:22:33,615
(woman laughs)

1812
01:22:33,615 --> 01:22:36,117
Dr. Conners, are you Lutheran?

1813
01:22:36,117 --> 01:22:38,119
Yes, I-I am a Lutheran

1814
01:22:38,119 --> 01:22:41,623
but, please,
call me Frank.

1815
01:22:41,623 --> 01:22:44,125
Frank, would you like
to say grace?

1816
01:22:48,630 --> 01:22:52,634
Unless you're not comfortable.

1817
01:22:52,634 --> 01:22:54,636
Absolutely.

1818
01:22:56,638 --> 01:22:58,640
(clears throat)

1819
01:23:04,145 --> 01:23:07,649
Two little mice fell
into a bucket of cream.

1820
01:23:09,401 --> 01:23:11,653
The first mouse quickly
gave up and drowned

1821
01:23:11,653 --> 01:23:14,155
but the second mouse,
he struggled so hard

1822
01:23:14,155 --> 01:23:16,658
that he eventually churned
that cream into butter

1823
01:23:16,658 --> 01:23:18,660
and he walked out.

1824
01:23:18,660 --> 01:23:21,663
Amen.

1825
01:23:21,663 --> 01:23:22,664
Amen.

1826
01:23:22,664 --> 01:23:25,667
Amen. Oh, that was beautiful.

1827
01:23:25,667 --> 01:23:28,670
The mouse, he churned
that cream into butter.

1828
01:23:28,670 --> 01:23:31,172
(sighing happily)

1829
01:23:31,172 --> 01:23:32,173
That's right.

1830
01:23:32,173 --> 01:23:33,675
That's pretty good.

1831
01:23:33,675 --> 01:23:35,176
Thank you.

1832
01:23:35,176 --> 01:23:37,178
Frank, have you decided
which hospital

1833
01:23:37,178 --> 01:23:38,680
you want to work at
here in New Orleans?

1834
01:23:38,680 --> 01:23:41,182
Well, um, to be
quite honest

1835
01:23:41,182 --> 01:23:44,185
I'm thinking about
getting back into law.

1836
01:23:44,185 --> 01:23:46,187
Oh, my!

1837
01:23:46,187 --> 01:23:48,189
Are you a doctor
or a lawyer?

1838
01:23:48,189 --> 01:23:50,692
Before I went
to medical school

1839
01:23:50,692 --> 01:23:52,694
I passed the bar
in California.

1840
01:23:52,694 --> 01:23:54,696
I practiced law for one year

1841
01:23:54,696 --> 01:23:58,199
then I decided why not
try my hand at pediatrics?

1842
01:23:58,199 --> 01:24:00,702
You're just
full of surprises.

1843
01:24:00,702 --> 01:24:01,703
Yeah.

1844
01:24:01,703 --> 01:24:04,205
MOTHER (laughing):
Oh, my.

1845
01:24:04,205 --> 01:24:05,206
A doctor and a lawyer.

1846
01:24:05,206 --> 01:24:07,208
Well, I'd say that Brenda
hit the jackpot.

1847
01:24:07,208 --> 01:24:10,211
Where did you go
to law school?

1848
01:24:10,211 --> 01:24:12,213
Uh, Berkeley.

1849
01:24:12,213 --> 01:24:13,214
(gasping)

1850
01:24:13,214 --> 01:24:14,716
Berkley, Berkley.
Oh, my gosh.

1851
01:24:14,716 --> 01:24:16,217
Isn't that where
you went, Daddy?

1852
01:24:16,217 --> 01:24:18,219
Maybe Frank could
come work for you, Roger.

1853
01:24:18,219 --> 01:24:19,721
You're always saying
how hard it is

1854
01:24:19,721 --> 01:24:21,222
to find
Assistant Prosecutors.

1855
01:24:21,222 --> 01:24:23,725
Could he, Daddy?
Could he, please?

1856
01:24:23,725 --> 01:24:25,226
Could he come
work with you, please?

1857
01:24:25,226 --> 01:24:27,228
Was that snake Hollingsworth
still teaching there

1858
01:24:27,228 --> 01:24:28,730
when you went
through Berkley?

1859
01:24:28,730 --> 01:24:30,231
(laughs quietly)

1860
01:24:30,231 --> 01:24:31,733
Hollingsworth.

1861
01:24:31,733 --> 01:24:34,736
Yes. Grumpy old
Hollingsworth, right?

1862
01:24:34,736 --> 01:24:36,237
I tell you.
Meaner than ever.

1863
01:24:36,738 --> 01:24:38,740
And that dog of his?

1864
01:24:41,242 --> 01:24:45,246
Tell me, Frank, what was
the name of his little dog?

1865
01:24:53,755 --> 01:24:57,258
I'm sorry. Uh...

1866
01:24:57,258 --> 01:24:59,260
The dog was dead.

1867
01:24:59,260 --> 01:25:00,762
(women cooing)

1868
01:25:00,762 --> 01:25:04,265
How unfortunate.

1869
01:25:04,265 --> 01:25:06,267
Yeah.

1870
01:25:36,798 --> 01:25:39,300
A doctor, a lawyer,
a Lutheran...

1871
01:25:42,303 --> 01:25:45,306
So what are you, Frank?

1872
01:25:45,306 --> 01:25:46,808
'Cause I think
you're about to ask

1873
01:25:47,308 --> 01:25:48,810
for my daughter's hand
in marriage

1874
01:25:48,810 --> 01:25:50,311
and I have a right to know.

1875
01:25:50,311 --> 01:25:52,814
Know what, sir?

1876
01:25:52,814 --> 01:25:55,316
The truth.

1877
01:25:55,316 --> 01:25:59,821
Tell me the
truth, Frank.

1878
01:25:59,821 --> 01:26:03,825
What are you
doing here?

1879
01:26:03,825 --> 01:26:06,828
What is a man like you
doing with Brenda?

1880
01:26:06,828 --> 01:26:09,330
If you want my blessing

1881
01:26:09,330 --> 01:26:11,332
if you want my daughter

1882
01:26:11,332 --> 01:26:14,335
I'd like to hear
it from you now.

1883
01:26:17,338 --> 01:26:19,340
The truth is, sir, that...

1884
01:26:22,844 --> 01:26:24,345
The truth is that...

1885
01:26:26,347 --> 01:26:29,851
I'm not a doctor,
I'm not a lawyer...

1886
01:26:32,353 --> 01:26:34,856
I'm not an airline pilot.

1887
01:26:35,356 --> 01:26:38,359
I'm... I'm nothing, really.

1888
01:26:43,865 --> 01:26:47,869
I'm-I'm-I'm just a kid who's
in love with your daughter.

1889
01:26:50,872 --> 01:26:53,374
No.

1890
01:27:01,382 --> 01:27:03,885
You know what you are?

1891
01:27:03,885 --> 01:27:05,887
You're a romantic.

1892
01:27:05,887 --> 01:27:08,890
Men like us are nothing
without the women we love.

1893
01:27:08,890 --> 01:27:11,893
I must confess, I'm guilty
of the same foolish whimsy.

1894
01:27:11,893 --> 01:27:13,895
I proposed to Carol
after five dates

1895
01:27:13,895 --> 01:27:17,398
with two nickels in my pockets
and holes in my shoes

1896
01:27:17,398 --> 01:27:19,901
because I knew
she was the one.

1897
01:27:19,901 --> 01:27:22,403
So go ahead, Frank.

1898
01:27:25,406 --> 01:27:27,909
Don't be afraid.

1899
01:27:27,909 --> 01:27:31,412
Ask the question
you came here to ask me.

1900
01:27:33,414 --> 01:27:35,917
Sir, uh, uh...

1901
01:27:35,917 --> 01:27:37,418
w-what would I have to do

1902
01:27:37,418 --> 01:27:39,921
to take the bar
here in New Orleans?

1903
01:27:39,921 --> 01:27:41,923
(laughing)

1904
01:27:44,926 --> 01:27:48,179
No, the... the other question.

1905
01:27:48,179 --> 01:27:51,933
(ticking)

1906
01:27:51,933 --> 01:27:55,937
WOMAN:
Right through
that door.

1907
01:27:55,937 --> 01:27:58,439
Good luck, Mr. Conners.

1908
01:27:58,439 --> 01:28:00,441
Thank you.

1909
01:28:07,949 --> 01:28:09,450
Hey, Frank...

1910
01:28:09,450 --> 01:28:11,452
you know what I could
never figure out?

1911
01:28:11,452 --> 01:28:14,455
How did you cheat on the
bar exam in Louisiana?

1912
01:28:14,455 --> 01:28:16,457
Why? What's the difference?

1913
01:28:16,457 --> 01:28:18,459
Someone else took the test
for you, didn't they?

1914
01:28:18,459 --> 01:28:21,462
Carl, I'm going to prison
for a long time.

1915
01:28:21,462 --> 01:28:23,965
Seriously,
what's the difference?

1916
01:28:23,965 --> 01:28:26,467
It's a simple question.

1917
01:28:26,467 --> 01:28:28,970
Are you going to eat
that eclair?

1918
01:28:31,472 --> 01:28:34,976
Yeah. I'm saving
it for later.

1919
01:28:34,976 --> 01:28:36,978
Well, you want
to split it with me?

1920
01:28:36,978 --> 01:28:40,481
No.

1921
01:28:40,481 --> 01:28:43,985
Give me half that eclair
and I'll tell you.

1922
01:28:53,494 --> 01:28:57,999
I'm going to figure it out
sooner or later.

1923
01:29:04,505 --> 01:29:08,009
You'll be working under
Phillip Rigby in corporate law.

1924
01:29:08,009 --> 01:29:11,012
Why don't you settle in,
organize your desk?

1925
01:29:13,514 --> 01:29:15,016
Thank you.

1926
01:29:15,016 --> 01:29:17,518
We're having lunch at 12:30
with the Attorney General

1927
01:29:17,518 --> 01:29:19,520
and Governor McKeithen.

1928
01:29:19,520 --> 01:29:21,022
Himself.

1929
01:29:21,022 --> 01:29:22,523
The Governor.

1930
01:29:22,523 --> 01:29:23,524
Did we
spell it right?

1931
01:29:23,524 --> 01:29:25,360
You sure did.

1932
01:29:25,360 --> 01:29:26,861
Congratulations.

1933
01:29:26,861 --> 01:29:28,363
Thank you, sir.

1934
01:29:28,363 --> 01:29:29,364
Welcome aboard.

1935
01:29:29,864 --> 01:29:31,866
Now...

1936
01:29:35,870 --> 01:29:38,373
Look at this photograph,
Mr. Stewart.

1937
01:29:38,373 --> 01:29:41,376
It's a photograph
of Prentice York

1938
01:29:41,376 --> 01:29:43,378
where they found him, dead.

1939
01:29:43,378 --> 01:29:47,382
Now, here is an enlargement
of part of that photograph.

1940
01:29:47,382 --> 01:29:49,884
This is a photograph
of the defendant's signature

1941
01:29:49,884 --> 01:29:51,386
on a canceled check.

1942
01:29:51,386 --> 01:29:53,888
Now, here is an enlargement
of that same signature

1943
01:29:53,888 --> 01:29:54,889
which matches

1944
01:29:55,390 --> 01:29:58,393
the signature on the letters
that he wrote to Mrs. Simon

1945
01:29:58,393 --> 01:29:59,894
which discuss the possibility

1946
01:29:59,894 --> 01:30:02,397
of defrauding
the great State of Louisiana.

1947
01:30:02,397 --> 01:30:03,398
Your Honor

1948
01:30:03,398 --> 01:30:05,400
ladies and gentlemen of the jury

1949
01:30:05,400 --> 01:30:07,402
this is irrefutable evidence

1950
01:30:07,402 --> 01:30:10,405
that the defendant is,
in fact, lying.

1951
01:30:10,905 --> 01:30:12,407
(echoing thud)

1952
01:30:12,407 --> 01:30:14,409
(chair slams against floor)

1953
01:30:15,410 --> 01:30:20,915
Mr. Conners, this is
a preliminary hearing.

1954
01:30:20,915 --> 01:30:24,919
There is no... defendant.

1955
01:30:24,919 --> 01:30:29,424
There is no... jury.

1956
01:30:29,424 --> 01:30:32,427
It's just me.

1957
01:30:32,427 --> 01:30:33,928
Son...

1958
01:30:33,928 --> 01:30:38,433
what in the hell
is wrong with you?!

1959
01:30:38,433 --> 01:30:40,435
(applause over TV)
Is that Mitch?

1960
01:30:40,435 --> 01:30:41,936
Roger! It's Mitch!

1961
01:30:41,936 --> 01:30:43,938
Oh, my, I lost
all track of time.

1962
01:30:43,938 --> 01:30:46,941
MITCH MILLER (on TV):
As studio guests
for the sing-along tonight

1963
01:30:46,941 --> 01:30:48,943
we have the children's choir
of St. Monica's Church

1964
01:30:48,943 --> 01:30:50,945
in New York City.

1965
01:30:50,945 --> 01:30:52,447
Won't you join them and the gang

1966
01:30:52,447 --> 01:30:54,949
in a few songs for the Irish?
Everybody!

1967
01:30:54,949 --> 01:30:57,452
? Has anybody here seen Kelly? ?

1968
01:30:57,452 --> 01:31:00,455
(all but Frank joining in):
? K, E, double L, Y ?

1969
01:31:00,455 --> 01:31:02,957
? Has anybody here seen Kelly? ?

1970
01:31:02,957 --> 01:31:04,959
? Have you seen him smile? ?

1971
01:31:04,959 --> 01:31:07,962
? Sure his hair is red,
and his eyes are blue ?

1972
01:31:07,962 --> 01:31:10,465
? And he's Irish
through and through ?

1973
01:31:10,465 --> 01:31:12,967
? Has anybody here seen Kelly ?

1974
01:31:12,967 --> 01:31:15,470
? Kelly from the Emerald Isle? ?

1975
01:31:15,470 --> 01:31:17,972
? Has anybody here seen Kelly? ?

1976
01:31:17,972 --> 01:31:20,475
? K, E, double L, Y ?

1977
01:31:20,475 --> 01:31:22,977
(joining in):
? Has anybody here seen Kelly? ?

1978
01:31:22,977 --> 01:31:25,480
? Have you seen him smile? ?

1979
01:31:25,480 --> 01:31:27,982
? Sure his hair is red,
and his eyes are blue ?

1980
01:31:27,982 --> 01:31:30,485
? And he's Irish
through and through ?

1981
01:31:30,485 --> 01:31:32,987
? Has anybody here
seen Kelly... ?

1982
01:31:32,987 --> 01:31:35,490
JUDY GARLAND (on record):
? Embrace me ?

1983
01:31:35,490 --> 01:31:40,995
? My sweet embraceable you ?

1984
01:31:40,995 --> 01:31:43,998
? Embrace me ?

1985
01:31:43,998 --> 01:31:50,505
? You irreplaceable you ?

1986
01:31:50,505 --> 01:31:53,508
? Just one look at you ?

1987
01:31:53,508 --> 01:31:59,514
? My heart grew tipsy in me ?

1988
01:31:59,514 --> 01:32:02,517
? You and you alone ?

1989
01:32:02,517 --> 01:32:09,023
? Bring out the gypsy in me ?

1990
01:32:09,023 --> 01:32:12,026
? I love all ?

1991
01:32:12,026 --> 01:32:18,533
? The many charms about you ?

1992
01:32:18,533 --> 01:32:21,536
? Above all ?

1993
01:32:21,536 --> 01:32:24,539
? I want my arms about you... ?

1994
01:32:24,539 --> 01:32:26,541
(whispers):
Dad.

1995
01:32:28,042 --> 01:32:31,045
? ...Don't be
a naughty baby... ?

1996
01:32:31,045 --> 01:32:33,047
What are you doing here?

1997
01:32:33,047 --> 01:32:37,552
I... I-I came to see you.

1998
01:32:37,552 --> 01:32:40,555
? ...My sweet embraceable... ?

1999
01:32:40,555 --> 01:32:43,057
What are you doing
dressed like this?

2000
01:32:43,057 --> 01:32:45,059
I took a job.
A government job.

2001
01:32:45,059 --> 01:32:46,060
You see what I'm doing?

2002
01:32:46,561 --> 01:32:48,062
Do you have a good lawyer?

2003
01:32:48,062 --> 01:32:50,565
Well... I sort of am
a lawyer now.

2004
01:32:50,565 --> 01:32:54,569
Look at this letter.
The IRS wants more.

2005
01:32:54,569 --> 01:32:57,071
I had a deal with them:
two penalties.

2006
01:32:57,071 --> 01:33:00,575
They ate the cake,
now they want the crumbs.

2007
01:33:00,575 --> 01:33:03,077
I want to sue them.

2008
01:33:03,077 --> 01:33:06,080
Now they want the crumbs.

2009
01:33:06,080 --> 01:33:08,082
They... Here, sit down.

2010
01:33:08,583 --> 01:33:11,085
They're trying to scare
me, intimidate me.

2011
01:33:11,085 --> 01:33:13,588
You know what?

2012
01:33:13,588 --> 01:33:17,091
You know what? I'll
make them chase me...

2013
01:33:17,091 --> 01:33:19,594
for the rest
of their lives.

2014
01:33:25,600 --> 01:33:29,103
Hey, it's great
to see you, Daddy.

2015
01:33:29,103 --> 01:33:33,608
Listen, sit down, I...
I want to show you something.

2016
01:33:35,610 --> 01:33:37,612
I came here
to give you this.

2017
01:33:37,612 --> 01:33:42,116
It's an invitation
to an engagement party.

2018
01:33:43,117 --> 01:33:46,120
Daddy, I'm getting married.

2019
01:33:46,120 --> 01:33:49,123
Can you believe that?
I'm getting married.

2020
01:33:49,123 --> 01:33:51,626
You don't need to worry
about anything now, Dad.

2021
01:33:51,626 --> 01:33:53,628
Listen, I'm getting
a brand-new Cadillac.

2022
01:33:53,628 --> 01:33:55,630
I'm getting a $60,000 house.

2023
01:33:55,630 --> 01:33:57,632
I'm-I'm getting it all back.

2024
01:33:57,632 --> 01:34:00,134
All-All the jewelry,
all the furs, everything, Dad.

2025
01:34:00,134 --> 01:34:02,637
Everything they took from us,
I'm going to get it back.

2026
01:34:03,137 --> 01:34:04,639
Now...

2027
01:34:04,639 --> 01:34:08,643
has Ma seen you
dressed like this?

2028
01:34:08,643 --> 01:34:12,146
Yeah, she came to
pick up some boxes.

2029
01:34:12,146 --> 01:34:13,648
That's okay, that's okay,
you know why?

2030
01:34:13,648 --> 01:34:15,650
'Cause she... she's going
to the wedding with us.

2031
01:34:16,150 --> 01:34:17,652
I'm going to get you
a brand-new suit, Dad.

2032
01:34:17,652 --> 01:34:19,153
I'm getting you
a brand-new suit.

2033
01:34:19,153 --> 01:34:20,655
One of those
Manhattan Eagle

2034
01:34:20,655 --> 01:34:21,656
three-button
black pearl suits.

2035
01:34:21,656 --> 01:34:22,657
You'll look great.

2036
01:34:22,657 --> 01:34:24,158
Those are nice. Yeah.

2037
01:34:24,158 --> 01:34:27,161
She won't see me.

2038
01:34:28,162 --> 01:34:29,664
Well, have you tried
to call her?

2039
01:34:29,664 --> 01:34:32,166
Uh-uh.

2040
01:34:32,166 --> 01:34:34,669
Why don't... why don't you
call her right now?

2041
01:34:34,669 --> 01:34:37,171
Dad, why don't you
call her right now? Here.

2042
01:34:37,171 --> 01:34:39,173
Dad, just call her.
Call her for me.

2043
01:34:39,173 --> 01:34:41,175
You call her,
and you tell her

2044
01:34:41,175 --> 01:34:43,678
I have two first-class tickets
to go see her son's wedding...

2045
01:34:43,678 --> 01:34:46,681
Your mother's married now,
to my friend Jack Barnes.

2046
01:34:46,681 --> 01:34:49,684
They have a house
in Long Island.

2047
01:34:49,684 --> 01:34:53,688
(whispering):
I had an FBI agent
come see me.

2048
01:34:53,688 --> 01:34:55,690
You got their number, son.

2049
01:34:55,690 --> 01:34:57,692
The guy looked scared.

2050
01:34:57,692 --> 01:35:02,196
The United States government,
champ, running for the hills.

2051
01:35:02,196 --> 01:35:04,699
Pow! To the moon!

2052
01:35:15,710 --> 01:35:18,713
Dad... it's over.

2053
01:35:20,214 --> 01:35:22,216
I'm going to stop now.

2054
01:35:22,216 --> 01:35:24,218
But y-you've...

2055
01:35:24,218 --> 01:35:26,220
They're never going
to catch you, Frank.

2056
01:35:26,220 --> 01:35:28,723
Why won't you
sit down?
Dad, she wouldn't do that.

2057
01:35:28,723 --> 01:35:30,725
Come on, sit.
Why would she do that to you?

2058
01:35:30,725 --> 01:35:32,226
Come on, sit with me.
Have a drink.

2059
01:35:32,226 --> 01:35:33,728
I'm your father.

2060
01:35:33,728 --> 01:35:37,231
Then ask me to stop.

2061
