01:57:28,207 --> 01:57:29,208
(speaking in French)

2563
01:57:29,208 --> 01:57:30,209
I'm... I'm
supposed to go.

2564
01:57:30,209 --> 01:57:31,711
Where are you
taking him?

2565
01:57:31,711 --> 01:57:33,212
Let me in the...

2566
01:57:33,212 --> 01:57:34,213
Let me in the car!

2567
01:57:34,213 --> 01:57:35,214
(shouting continues)

2568
01:57:35,214 --> 01:57:37,717
Hey! Let me in the car!

2569
01:57:37,717 --> 01:57:38,718
? Gloria... ?

2570
01:57:38,718 --> 01:57:39,719
(engine starts)

2571
01:57:39,719 --> 01:57:41,220
Don't worry, Frank!

2572
01:57:41,220 --> 01:57:43,222
I'll have you extradited
back to the United States.

2573
01:57:43,222 --> 01:57:44,223
Don't worry.

2574
01:57:44,223 --> 01:57:46,726
(siren wailing)

2575
01:57:49,228 --> 01:57:57,737
? Gloria ?

2576
01:57:57,737 --> 01:58:04,744
? In excelsius Deo. ?

2577
01:58:04,744 --> 01:58:07,747
Carl...

2578
01:58:07,747 --> 01:58:10,249
Carl, you have
to remember

2579
01:58:10,249 --> 01:58:13,753
to let me call my father
when we land.

2580
01:58:13,753 --> 01:58:15,755
I just want to,
I want to talk to him

2581
01:58:15,755 --> 01:58:18,758
before he sees me on television
or something like that.

2582
01:58:28,768 --> 01:58:30,269
Carl, look.

2583
01:58:30,269 --> 01:58:32,772
That's LaGuardia right there.

2584
01:58:32,772 --> 01:58:34,273
Runway 4-4.

2585
01:58:34,273 --> 01:58:36,776
Frank, your
father is dead.

2586
01:58:36,776 --> 01:58:38,778
I'm sorry.

2587
01:58:38,778 --> 01:58:40,780
I didn't want
to say anything

2588
01:58:40,780 --> 01:58:42,782
till we got
closer to home.

2589
01:58:42,782 --> 01:58:45,284
He-He... He fell
down some steps

2590
01:58:45,284 --> 01:58:49,288
at Grand Central Station
trying to catch a train.

2591
01:58:49,288 --> 01:58:51,791
I didn't want to be
the one to tell you.

2592
01:58:51,791 --> 01:58:55,294
You're lying, right?

2593
01:58:55,294 --> 01:58:57,296
You said
I could talk to him.

2594
01:58:57,296 --> 01:58:58,297
Carl, who are you to...

2595
01:58:58,297 --> 01:59:00,299
who are you to say
something like that, huh?

2596
01:59:00,299 --> 01:59:02,301
Who are you
to say something like that?

2597
01:59:02,301 --> 01:59:03,302
You said
I could talk to him.

2598
01:59:03,302 --> 01:59:05,304
He fell, and he...
and he broke his neck.

2599
01:59:05,304 --> 01:59:07,807
I'm sorry.

2600
01:59:07,807 --> 01:59:10,309
I'm really sorry.

2601
01:59:17,817 --> 01:59:20,820
(panting)

2602
01:59:20,820 --> 01:59:21,821
(hits seat)

2603
01:59:21,821 --> 01:59:23,823
(sobbing):
Goddamn it!

2604
01:59:23,823 --> 01:59:25,825
Carl, I'm going to be sick!

2605
01:59:25,825 --> 01:59:27,326
(people muttering)
It's all right.

2606
01:59:27,326 --> 01:59:28,327
It's all right.
It's okay.

2607
01:59:28,327 --> 01:59:29,829
Carl, I got to go
to the bathroom.

2608
01:59:29,829 --> 01:59:30,830
I'm going to be sick.

2609
01:59:30,830 --> 01:59:32,331
Sure.
Let's go in the bathroom.

2610
01:59:33,833 --> 01:59:35,835
(panting)

2611
01:59:39,338 --> 01:59:40,840
Goddamn it!

2612
01:59:40,840 --> 01:59:44,844
(sobbing)

2613
01:59:44,844 --> 01:59:46,345
(pounding)

2614
01:59:46,345 --> 01:59:47,847
(murmuring)

2615
01:59:47,847 --> 01:59:50,349
(panting)

2616
01:59:50,349 --> 01:59:52,852
(panting slows)

2617
01:59:53,853 --> 01:59:55,855
(Frank panting)

2618
01:59:58,357 --> 02:00:01,360
(whispering):
Oh, Daddy...

2619
02:00:03,863 --> 02:00:05,364
You'll have take your seat, sir.

2620
02:00:05,865 --> 02:00:07,366
I've told you twice.
We're landing.

2621
02:00:07,366 --> 02:00:08,868
Sorry. Thank you...
All of you.

2622
02:00:08,868 --> 02:00:09,869
Frank! Come on now.

2623
02:00:09,869 --> 02:00:11,370
Frank?
We're landing in six minutes.

2624
02:00:11,370 --> 02:00:12,872
All of you need to be
in your seats

2625
02:00:12,872 --> 02:00:15,374
Frank, open the door!
with your seat belts fastened.

2626
02:00:15,374 --> 02:00:16,876
Frank!

2627
02:00:18,878 --> 02:00:20,379
You do it.
Yeah.

2628
02:00:32,892 --> 02:00:35,394
(engines decelerating)

2629
02:00:41,901 --> 02:00:44,403
(grunting)

2630
02:00:47,406 --> 02:00:48,407
(frustrated sigh)

2631
02:00:48,407 --> 02:00:49,909
(grunting)

2632
02:00:49,909 --> 02:00:51,911
Frank! Frank!

2633
02:00:51,911 --> 02:00:53,913
(engines roaring)

2634
02:00:53,913 --> 02:00:56,415
(tires squealing)

2635
02:00:56,415 --> 02:00:58,918
HANRATTY:
All right, remain seated,
everyone, please.

2636
02:00:58,918 --> 02:01:00,920
FBI. Stay seated.
FBI. Stay seated.

2637
02:01:00,920 --> 02:01:03,923
(engines whining)

2638
02:01:08,928 --> 02:01:10,429
Please remain seated!
Stay seated.

2639
02:01:10,429 --> 02:01:11,931
STEWARDESS:
You must stay seated

2640
02:01:11,931 --> 02:01:14,433
until the aircraft
has come to a complete stop.

2641
02:01:14,433 --> 02:01:15,935
HANRATTY:
God almighty.

2642
02:01:15,935 --> 02:01:19,939
NAT KING COLE:
? Chestnuts roasting
on an open fire... ?

2643
02:01:19,939 --> 02:01:22,942
(panting)

2644
02:01:22,942 --> 02:01:30,116
? Jack Frost nipping
at your nose ?

2645
02:01:30,116 --> 02:01:35,621
? Yuletide carols
being sung by a choir ?

2646
02:01:35,621 --> 02:01:41,127
? And folks dressed up
like Eskimos ?

2647
02:01:41,127 --> 02:01:44,130
? Everybody knows ?

2648
02:01:44,130 --> 02:01:49,635
? A turkey and some mistletoe ?

2649
02:01:49,635 --> 02:01:54,140
? Help to make
the season bright ?

2650
02:01:54,140 --> 02:01:56,642
(quietly blowing notes)

2651
02:01:56,642 --> 02:02:01,147
? Tiny tots with their eyes
all aglow ?

2652
02:02:01,147 --> 02:02:05,151
? Will find it hard
to sleep tonight... ?

2653
02:02:05,151 --> 02:02:07,153
What's your name?

2654
02:02:07,153 --> 02:02:10,156
(blows note)
? They know that Santa's
on his way... ?

2655
02:02:10,156 --> 02:02:13,659
Where's your mommy?

2656
02:02:13,659 --> 02:02:18,164
? ...He's loaded lots of toys
and goodies on his sleigh ?

2657
02:02:18,164 --> 02:02:21,167
(blows note)

2658
02:02:21,167 --> 02:02:26,672
? And every mother's child
is gonna spy ?

2659
02:02:26,672 --> 02:02:29,175
? To see if reindeer
really know how to fly... ?

2660
02:02:29,175 --> 02:02:32,178
(brakes squeaking)

2661
02:02:32,178 --> 02:02:37,683
? And so I'm offering
this simple phrase... ?

2662
02:02:37,683 --> 02:02:40,686
(men shouting indistinctly)

2663
02:02:40,686 --> 02:02:47,193
? To kids from one to 92 ?

2664
02:02:47,193 --> 02:02:50,696
? Although it's been said
many times ?

2665
02:02:50,696 --> 02:02:54,200
? Many ways:
"Merry Christmas..." ?

2666
02:02:54,200 --> 02:02:55,701
Hands behind your head!

2667
02:02:55,701 --> 02:02:57,703
? ...To you. ?

2668
02:02:57,703 --> 02:02:59,205
Carl, get me in the car,
please.

2669
02:02:59,205 --> 02:03:02,708
Get me in the car.

2670
02:03:02,708 --> 02:03:04,710
HANRATTY:
Put him in.

2671
02:03:04,710 --> 02:03:07,713
(piano playing interlude
in "The Christmas Song")

2672
02:03:07,713 --> 02:03:09,715
(handcuffs latching)

2673
02:03:19,225 --> 02:03:20,726
? ?

2674
02:03:20,726 --> 02:03:24,230
JUDGE:
Taking into account
the gravity of these crimes

2675
02:03:24,230 --> 02:03:28,234
your history of bold
and elusive behavior

2676
02:03:28,234 --> 02:03:30,236
and your complete lack
of respect

2677
02:03:30,236 --> 02:03:32,738
for the laws
of the United States

2678
02:03:32,738 --> 02:03:36,242
I have no choice
but to ignore your request

2679
02:03:36,242 --> 02:03:38,244
to be treated as a minor

2680
02:03:38,244 --> 02:03:39,745
and sentence you to 12 years

2681
02:03:39,745 --> 02:03:43,249
in Atlanta's
maximum security prison

2682
02:03:43,249 --> 02:03:46,752
and recommend strongly
that you be kept in isolation

2683
02:03:46,752 --> 02:03:48,754
for the entirety
of that sentence.

2684
02:03:48,754 --> 02:03:52,258
? ..."Merry Christmas to you." ?

2685
02:03:52,258 --> 02:03:55,761
(song ends with guitar playing
"Jingle Bells" riff)

2686
02:04:01,016 --> 02:04:03,018
Use that door
over there.

2687
02:04:03,018 --> 02:04:05,521
(phone ringing)

2688
02:04:05,521 --> 02:04:08,524
(indistinct voices)

2689
02:04:08,524 --> 02:04:10,526
PRISONER:
...and give
everyone my love.

2690
02:04:10,526 --> 02:04:12,528
I think about them
all the time.

2691
02:04:23,038 --> 02:04:25,040
(indistinct conversations
in distance)

2692
02:04:29,545 --> 02:04:31,046
(sighs deeply)

2693
02:04:31,046 --> 02:04:33,299
Merry Christmas, Frank.

2694
02:04:35,551 --> 02:04:38,554
Hey, I got you
some comic books here.

2695
02:04:45,060 --> 02:04:46,061
How's your daughter?

2696
02:04:46,562 --> 02:04:47,563
What was her name?

2697
02:04:47,563 --> 02:04:48,564
Grace.

2698
02:04:48,564 --> 02:04:50,065
Well... I don't know.

2699
02:04:50,065 --> 02:04:52,067
She lives with her mother
in Chicago

2700
02:04:52,067 --> 02:04:54,069
and I don't
get to see her much.

2701
02:04:55,571 --> 02:04:57,072
What's in the briefcase?

2702
02:04:57,072 --> 02:04:59,074
Oh. I'm on my way
to the airport.

2703
02:04:59,074 --> 02:05:01,076
It's a paperhanger

2704
02:05:01,076 --> 02:05:03,579
who's working his way
through Minnesota.

2705
02:05:03,579 --> 02:05:05,080
(chuckling)

2706
02:05:05,080 --> 02:05:08,584
Aw, geez, he's...
he's driving us crazy.

2707
02:05:08,584 --> 02:05:10,085
You got any of the checks?

2708
02:05:10,085 --> 02:05:12,588
Yeah, yeah, I got a...
a counterfeit that he drew

2709
02:05:12,588 --> 02:05:14,590
on the Great Lakes
Savings and Loan.

2710
02:05:14,590 --> 02:05:16,592
See, he's just using
a stencil machine

2711
02:05:16,592 --> 02:05:18,093
and an Underwood.

2712
02:05:18,093 --> 02:05:20,596
Yeah, it's a teller
at the bank.

2713
02:05:20,596 --> 02:05:22,097
Say again?

2714
02:05:22,097 --> 02:05:23,599
I-It's definitely
a teller, Carl.

2715
02:05:23,599 --> 02:05:25,601
I mean, banks, they
always use hand-stamps

2716
02:05:25,601 --> 02:05:27,102
for the dates, see.

2717
02:05:27,102 --> 02:05:29,104
They get used
over and over again

2718
02:05:29,104 --> 02:05:30,606
so they always get worn out

2719
02:05:30,606 --> 02:05:32,107
and the numbers
are always cracking.

2720
02:05:32,608 --> 02:05:34,109
The sixes and the nines...

2721
02:05:34,109 --> 02:05:36,111
see, they go first.

2722
02:05:38,113 --> 02:05:40,115
Thanks.

2723
02:05:40,115 --> 02:05:42,117
(buzzer sounding)

2724
02:05:44,620 --> 02:05:47,623
MAN:
I'd like you to take a look
at something for me.

2725
02:05:52,628 --> 02:05:54,630
Tell me
what you think.

2726
02:05:54,630 --> 02:05:57,132
(clears throat)

2727
02:05:57,132 --> 02:05:58,634
That's a fake.

2728
02:05:58,634 --> 02:06:00,636
How do you know?

2729
02:06:00,636 --> 02:06:01,637
You haven't
looked at it.

2730
02:06:01,637 --> 02:06:04,139
Well, there's
no perforated edge, right?

2731
02:06:04,139 --> 02:06:07,142
I mean, this... this check
was hand-cut, not fed.

2732
02:06:07,142 --> 02:06:09,645
Yeah...

2733
02:06:09,645 --> 02:06:10,646
Paper is double-bonded

2734
02:06:10,646 --> 02:06:13,148
much too heavy
to be a bank check.

2735
02:06:13,148 --> 02:06:17,152
Magnetic ink, it's, uh,
raised against my fingers

2736
02:06:17,152 --> 02:06:18,654
instead of flat.

2737
02:06:18,654 --> 02:06:19,655
(sniffing)

2738
02:06:19,655 --> 02:06:21,156
And this doesn't
smell like MICR.

2739
02:06:21,156 --> 02:06:22,157
It's some kind of a...

2740
02:06:22,157 --> 02:06:24,159
you know, some kind
of a drafting ink.

2741
02:06:24,159 --> 02:06:26,161
You know, the kind you get
at a stationery store.

2742
02:06:26,161 --> 02:06:27,663
(clears throat)

2743
02:06:30,165 --> 02:06:32,167
(paper rustling)

2744
02:06:32,167 --> 02:06:34,169
Frank...

2745
02:06:34,169 --> 02:06:36,171
would you be interested
in working

2746
02:06:36,171 --> 02:06:38,173
with the FBI's
Financial Crimes Unit?

2747
02:06:38,173 --> 02:06:40,175
(shuffles cards)

2748
02:06:40,175 --> 02:06:41,176
I already got a job here.

2749
02:06:41,176 --> 02:06:42,678
You know, I, uh,
deliver the mail.

2750
02:06:44,680 --> 02:06:49,685
Frank, we have the power
to take you out of prison.

2751
02:06:49,685 --> 02:06:51,186
You'd be placed in
the custody of the FBI

2752
02:06:51,186 --> 02:06:53,689
where you'd serve out the
remainder of your sentence

2753
02:06:53,689 --> 02:06:55,190
as an employee of
the federal government.

2754
02:06:57,693 --> 02:07:00,195
Under whose custody?

2755
02:07:06,201 --> 02:07:08,704
(phone ringing)

2756
02:07:08,704 --> 02:07:11,206
Hi. I-I'm Frank Abagnale.

2757
02:07:11,206 --> 02:07:13,709
I'm supposed to start work
here today.

2758
02:07:13,709 --> 02:07:16,712
It's a tour company
operating out of the BVI.

2759
02:07:16,712 --> 02:07:18,714
Sir, Mr. Abagnale
is here.

2760
02:07:18,714 --> 02:07:20,215
I'm going
to call you back.

2761
02:07:30,225 --> 02:07:33,228
(melancholy melody playing)

2762
02:07:41,737 --> 02:07:45,741
? ?

2763
02:07:50,245 --> 02:07:52,247
Hello, Carl.

2764
02:07:52,247 --> 02:07:54,249
Welcome to the FBI.

2765
02:07:54,249 --> 02:07:56,251
I'll show you
where you're working.

2766
02:08:03,759 --> 02:08:06,762
Carl... how long
do I have to work here?

2767
02:08:07,262 --> 02:08:09,765
It's 8:15 in the morning
to 5:00 in the afternoon.

2768
02:08:09,765 --> 02:08:11,767
45 minutes for lunch.

2769
02:08:11,767 --> 02:08:13,769
No, I...

2770
02:08:13,769 --> 02:08:15,771
I mean, how long?

2771
02:08:17,773 --> 02:08:19,775
Every day.

2772
02:08:19,775 --> 02:08:22,277
Every day, Frank,
till we let you go.

2773
02:08:32,287 --> 02:08:37,292
? ?

2774
02:08:46,301 --> 02:08:50,305
? ?

2775
02:09:00,315 --> 02:09:04,820
? ?

2776
02:09:13,829 --> 02:09:16,331
(tapping)
Yeah.

2777
02:09:16,331 --> 02:09:19,334
Hey, Carl.
Hi.

2778
02:09:19,334 --> 02:09:21,837
How you doing?

2779
02:09:21,837 --> 02:09:22,838
It's not a good
time, Frank.

2780
02:09:22,838 --> 02:09:24,840
I'm clearing my desk
for the weekend.

2781
02:09:27,843 --> 02:09:30,846
Carl, you mind if I come
to work with you tomorrow?

2782
02:09:30,846 --> 02:09:32,848
Tomorrow is Saturday.

2783
02:09:32,848 --> 02:09:35,350
I'm flying to Chicago
to see my daughter.

2784
02:09:35,350 --> 02:09:36,852
I'll be back
to work on Monday.

2785
02:09:36,852 --> 02:09:37,853
You're going
to see Grace, huh?

2786
02:09:37,853 --> 02:09:39,354
Well, that's the plan.

2787
02:09:41,857 --> 02:09:43,358
(heavy sigh)

2788
02:09:43,358 --> 02:09:45,360
So what should
I do till Monday?

2789
02:09:45,360 --> 02:09:47,362
I'm sorry, kid, I
can't help you there.

2790
02:09:47,362 --> 02:09:48,363
Excuse me.

2791
02:09:51,366 --> 02:09:54,870
(phone rings)

2792
02:09:54,870 --> 02:09:57,372
This is Hanratty.

2793
02:09:57,372 --> 02:09:59,374
Oh, yeah, put him on.

2794
02:10:07,382 --> 02:10:09,384
Mr. Sawyer.

2795
02:10:09,384 --> 02:10:11,386
How are you?

2796
02:10:11,386 --> 02:10:13,388
I have a half a dozen
more checks

2797
02:10:13,388 --> 02:10:15,390
on that tour operator
at the BVI.

2798
02:10:22,815 --> 02:10:24,817
(laughs quietly)

2799
02:10:34,827 --> 02:10:38,330
? ?

2800
02:10:38,330 --> 02:10:40,332
(opens and shuts drawer)

2801
02:10:48,841 --> 02:10:51,343
WOMAN (over P.A.):
American Airlines 355

2802
02:10:51,343 --> 02:10:53,846
serving Chicago
and San Francisco

2803
02:10:53,846 --> 02:10:55,347
is now open
for passenger check-in.

2804
02:10:55,848 --> 02:10:58,851
How'd you do it, Frank?

2805
02:10:58,851 --> 02:11:02,354
How'd you pass the bar
in Louisiana?

2806
02:11:02,354 --> 02:11:04,857
What are you doing here?

2807
02:11:04,857 --> 02:11:06,859
Listen...

2808
02:11:06,859 --> 02:11:08,861
I'm sorry I put you
through all this.

2809
02:11:08,861 --> 02:11:11,864
You go back to Europe, you're
gonna die in Perpignan Prison.

2810
02:11:11,864 --> 02:11:13,365
You try to run
here in the States

2811
02:11:13,365 --> 02:11:15,868
we'll send you
back to Atlanta for 50 years.

2812
02:11:15,868 --> 02:11:18,871
I know that.

2813
02:11:18,871 --> 02:11:21,373
I spent four years trying
to arrange your release.

2814
02:11:21,874 --> 02:11:23,375
Had to convince my bosses
at the FBI

2815
02:11:23,375 --> 02:11:25,878
and the Attorney General
of the United States

2816
02:11:25,878 --> 02:11:26,879
you wouldn't run.

2817
02:11:26,879 --> 02:11:29,882
Why'd you do it?

2818
02:11:29,882 --> 02:11:30,883
You're just a kid.

2819
02:11:30,883 --> 02:11:32,885
I'm not your kid.

2820
02:11:32,885 --> 02:11:35,387
You said you were
going to Chicago.

2821
02:11:35,387 --> 02:11:37,389
My daughter can't see me
this weekend.

2822
02:11:37,389 --> 02:11:39,391
She's going skiing.

2823
02:11:39,391 --> 02:11:40,893
You said she was
four years old.

2824
02:11:40,893 --> 02:11:41,894
You're lying.

2825
02:11:42,394 --> 02:11:43,896
She was four
when I left.

2826
02:11:43,896 --> 02:11:45,397
Now she's 15.

2827
02:11:45,397 --> 02:11:48,400
My wife's been remarried
for 11 years.

2828
02:11:48,400 --> 02:11:50,903
I see Grace
every now and again.

2829
02:11:50,903 --> 02:11:52,905
I don't understand.

2830
02:11:52,905 --> 02:11:54,907
Sure you do.

2831
02:11:54,907 --> 02:11:57,409
Sometimes it's easier
living the lie.

2832
02:12:00,913 --> 02:12:03,916
I'm going to let you
fly tonight, Frank.

2833
02:12:03,916 --> 02:12:05,918
I'm not even going
to try to stop you.

2834
02:12:05,918 --> 02:12:07,920
That's 'cause I know
you'll be back on Monday.

2835
02:12:07,920 --> 02:12:11,423
Yeah? How do you know
I'll come back?

2836
02:12:11,423 --> 02:12:14,426
(chuckles quietly)

2837
02:12:14,426 --> 02:12:16,428
Look.

2838
02:12:16,428 --> 02:12:18,430
Frank...

2839
02:12:18,430 --> 02:12:20,933
nobody's chasing you.

2840
02:12:20,933 --> 02:12:24,937
